      • setFeeding

        public static boolean setFeeding(java.lang.String tankId,
                                 boolean[][] weekArr,
                                 int[] hour,
                                 int[] minute,
                                 boolean auto,
                                 boolean manual)
        Sets the Feed xml data on the server using the given arguments. Each row of a week is associated to an row of hour and minute. Example of how to use the following function: 
         
 final boolean[][] weekArr = {
  		{ true, false, true, true, true, false, false },
  		{ false, true, false, true, false, false, false } 
 };

 final int[] hour = { 13, 07 };
 final int[] minute = { 50, 30 };

 
 
 FishyClient.setFeeding(tankID2, weekArr, hour, minute, offMin, true, false);
        This will update the xml to contain the following information: 
         
 <Feed auto="true" manual="false" schedules="2">
 		<details Fri="true" Mon="true" Sat="false" Sun="false" Thu="true" Tue="false" Wed="true" hr="13" min="50"/>
 		<details Fri="false" Mon="false" Sat="false" Sun="false" Thu="true" Tue="true" Wed="false" hr="7" min="30"/>
 </Feed>
        Parameters:
        tankId - the TankID of the tank
        weekArr - days of the week to feed
        hour - hour of the day to feed
        minute - minute of the hour to feed
        auto - set automatic feeding
        manual - send manual feeding
        Returns:
        true if successful, false otherwise

      • setLighting

        public static boolean setLighting(java.lang.String tankId,
                                  int[] onHr,
                                  int[] onMin,
                                  int[] offHr,
                                  int[] offMin,
                                  boolean autoLight,
                                  boolean manualLight)
        Sets the light xml data on the server using the given arguments. Each element in the arrays are associated to each other 1 to 1 for each details row. Example of how to use the following function: 
         
 
 final int[] onHr = { 12, 30 };
 final int[] onMin = { 12, 00 };
 
 final int[] offHr = { 12, 18 };
 final int[] offMin = { 30, 30 };
 
 
 FishyClient.setLighting(tankID2, onHr, onMin, offHr, offMin, true, false);
        This will update the xml to contain the following information: 
         
 <Light auto="true" manual="false" schedules="2">
 		<details offHr="12" offMin="30" onHr="12" onMin="12"/>
 		<details offHr="18" offMin="30" onHr="30" onMin="0"/>
 </Light>
        Parameters:
        tankId - the TankID of the tank that needs updating
        onHr - an array of hours to turn on
        onMin - an array of mins to turn on
        offHr - an array of hours to turn off
        offMin - an array of mins to turn off
        autoLight - boolean to save
        manualLight - boolean to save
        Returns:
        true if successful, false otherwise

      • appendActionLog

        public static boolean appendActionLog(java.lang.String tankId,
                                      java.lang.String[] date,
                                      java.lang.String[] desc,
                                      java.lang.String[] type)
        Append a list of logs to the sensor xml. * Example of how to use the following function: 
         
 String[] desc = {
 		"FEEDACTIVE",
 		"TEMPRANGE",
 		"MANFEEDING",
 		"FEEDACTIVE"
 };
 
 String[] type = {
 		"ACT",
 		"NOT",
 		"MANACT",
 		"ACT"
 };
 
 
 FishyClient.appendActionLog(tankID2, weekArr, hour, minute, offMin, true, false);
        This will update the xml to contain the following information: 
         
 <Logs>
 		<Log date="2017-02-20T19:19:19+0500" desc="FEEDACTIVE" type="ACT"/>
 		<Log date="2017-02-20T20:19:19+0500" desc="TEMPRANGE" type="NOT"/>
 		<Log date="2017-02-20T21:19:19+0500" desc="MANFEEDING" type="MANACT"/>
 </Logs>
        Parameters:
        tankId - the tankId
        date - the date of the log
        desc - the desc enum
        type - the type enum
        Returns:
        true if successful, false otherwise
